snippet.textDisplay:
Baro Mase Baro Phul Re Fuitya Thake Daale Re
A new bloom for every season blushing all around.

Ei Ponthe Aisey Nagor Porti Sondhya Kaale Re
My darling walks in here, when the sun has gone down.

Dekhite Sonar Nagor Go Chandero Soman
O, my charming lover, you look, as lovely as the moon.
Ful Futeche Gondhe Sara Mon
Flowers in the bloom; scents enthralling

Tumi Amar Koto Je Apon
O beloved, you are my dearest darling!

Dekha Na Dile Bondhu Kotha Koiyo Na
If you don’t show up, dear, then, don’t speak to me again!

Baro Mase Baro Phul Re Fuitya Thake Daale Re
A new bloom for every season blushing all around.

Ei Ponthe Aisey Nagor Porti Sondhya Kaale Re
My darling walks in here when the sun has gone down.
Kon Ba Deshe Thake Bhomra Kon Bagane Bose
Who knows where that bee lives; who knows in which orchard.
Kon Ba Phuler Modhu Khaite Uirya Uirya Ashe
He comes flying in to drink; who knows what sweet nectar!
Dekhite Sonar Nagor Go Chandero Soman
O, my charming lover, you look as lovely as the moon!

Hausher Piriti Korilam Ami
An affair of desire, that’s what I did.
Premi Jibon Premi Moron Ei Toh Jani Na
Love is life, love is death, that’s what I believed.
Pakhi Ure Gele Taar Danate Ki Bhoy
Since the bird would fly off, why fear her wings?

Ure Ure Jacche Sobai Bedonari Khoy
All fly away some day; all wither in pain.
Dekha Na Dile Bondhu Katha Koiyo Na
If you don’t show up, dear, then, don’t speak to me again!
